# LSan (LeakSanitizer) suppression file for mercury tests.
#
# These suppress benign leaks in third-party libraries that are out of
# our control and not actionable.
#
# This file is NOT applied globally.  It is only referenced by
# specific CI jobs that need to tolerate known OpenSSL init leaks
# (via LSAN_OPTIONS=suppressions=test/lsan.supp).

# OpenSSL 3.x one-time global allocations (error strings, algorithms,
# config, etc.) that are never freed by design.
leak:CRYPTO_malloc
